"'''Death Masque'''" was an original comic story by [[Steve Moore]] that was published in [[The Empire Strikes Back Monthly 149|''The Empire Strikes Back Monthly'' 149]]. "Death Masque" was one of the few original stories published in the UK series. Unlike the other original stories, it was not reprinted in the ''[[Classic Star Wars: Devilworlds]]'' series. For over 30 years, it and the [[1988]] ''[[Ewoks Annual]]'' were among the only licensed ''Star Wars'' stories in any medium to never be officially released in the United States. It was finally collected in ''[[Star Wars Omnibus: Wild Space Volume 1]]'' in 2013.

==Plot summary==
[[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial Forces]], led by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Dirk Balor]] attempt to capture [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] in the [[Lapez system/Legends|Lapez system]]. [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE fighters]] are unable to catch the elusive rebel, and Balor is forced to turn to a specialist, [[Altin Wuho]], and his pet [[nightmare demon]], [[Reist]]. Reist is sent in a small pod which lands on Skywalker's ship. Reist's ability causes Luke to experience severe hallucinations, eventually causing him to crash on [[Lapez 3]]. Luke's hallucinations continue, and he witnesses his friends, [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]], die before his very eyes.

Luke tries to fight the visions with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], but he is unable to stop the hallucinations. Eventually, the ghost of [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Ben Kenobi]] appears to Luke and tells him to turn the Force on himself. Luke obeys, and the hallucinations disintegrate to show Reist perched on Luke's chest. Skywalker activates his [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] and cuts the demon off his chest. At the same time, Altin Wuho arrives on the planet to retrieve his pet. He shoots Luke's [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] out of his hand, and Luke dives for cover. Just then, Reist reveals himself to be [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] and with his dying breath, he reveals to Luke that Wuho is a droid as a final revenge on his cruel master. Luke throws his lightsaber into the droid's chest, deactivating him. Luke uses parts from the destroyed droid to repair his crashed [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] and departs from Lapez 3.

